{"id": 16361, "date": "1987-03-29T11:00:00", "date_gmt": "1987-03-29T19:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=16361"}, "modified": "2026-06-10T13:49:07", "modified_gmt": "2026-06-10T20:49:07", "slug": "matr-patti-scialfa-and-bruce-springsteen-tell-him", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/03/29/matr-patti-scialfa-and-bruce-springsteen-tell-him/", "title": {"rendered": "Tell Him"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>It&#8217;s 1984, and a red-headed woman walks into a bar.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s let Bruce tell the story:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/QHNwh7Nhke8?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Bruce told that story virtually every night on Broadway. Given how special that song must be to them, you&#8217;d think we could practically trip over recordings of Bruce and Patti performing it together.</p>\n<p>But even though they&#8217;re known to have performed it a dozen times together in the 21st century, it&#8217;s pretty tough to find a recording of even one of them. That&#8217;s because almost every single one of those times was at a private benefit concert&#8211;either for the Rumson Country Day School and the Ranney School (where their kids attended), or Boston College (Evan&#8217;s alma mater). Once they even sang it at a wedding.</p>\n<p>In fact the only performance of those dozen that was open to the public was their holiday show at Harry&#8217;s Roadhouse in Asbury Park on December 19, 2004. At the late show that night, Bruce and Patti finally performed the song that changed their lives in public. Take a listen below&#8211;you&#8217;ll hear Patti on lead vocals, Bruce on backing vocals.</p>\n<div id=\"v-biU0S8St-1\" class=\"video-player\"><iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='758' height='426' src='https://videopress.com/embed/biU0S8St?hd=1&amp;cover=1&amp;loop=0&amp;autoPlay=0&amp;permalink=1&amp;muted=0&amp;controls=1&amp;playsinline=0&amp;useAverageColor=0&amp;preloadContent=metadata' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen data-resize-to-parent=\"true\" allow='clipboard-write'></iframe><script data-jetpack-boost=\"ignore\" src='https://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/video/assets/js/next/videopress-iframe.js'></script></div>\n<p>As for the original version of &#8220;Tell Him,&#8221; Bruce was technically correct in crediting The Exciters&#8211;they took the song all the way to #4 on the Billboard Hot 100 in early 1963.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/G2sH6h0ViDg?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>But the song actually dates back a little earlier under a slightly different name. In 1962, months before The Exciters released their version, Gil Hamilton first recorded the song as &#8220;Tell Her.&#8221; Other than the flipped gender, the lyrics are identical, but The Exciters&#8217; version is far more, well, exciting.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/9l06SeU48CE?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>And as for that fateful performance back in 1984&#8230; well, nothing came of it that night. But not long after, Bruce would invite Patti to join the E Street Band mere days before starting their biggest-ever tour.</p>\n<p>The rest is well-documented history.</p>\n<p><strong>Tell Him</strong><br />\n<strong>First performed:</strong> April 13, 2002 (Asbury Park, NJ)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> May 30, 2015 (Oakland, NJ)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 March 22, 2020</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>In 1984, a redheaded woman walked into a bar and changed the course of Bruce Springsteen&#8217;s life. This is the song she sang, and their only circulating performance of it together. </p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 69842, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_feature_clip_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}